content.problemStatement:
Which of the following code snippets correctly uses chained assignment to assign the value `300` to all three variables `x`, `y`, and `z`?

 **A.**

```c
int x = 300;
int y = 300;
int z = 300;
```

**B.**

```c
int x, y, z;
x = 300 = y = z;
```

 **C.**

```c
int x, y, z;
x = y;
y = z;
z = 300;
```

**D.**

```c
int x, y, z;
x = y = z = 300;
```

